{"FIORD":[{"def":"A narrow inlet of the sea, penetrating between high banks or rocks, as on the coasts of Norway and Alaska.","pos":""}],"FIORIN":[{"def":"A species of creeping bent grass (Agrostis alba); -- called also fiorin grass.","pos":""}],"FIORITE":[{"def":"A variety of opal occuring in the cavities of volcanic tufa, in smooth and shining globular and botryoidal masses, having a pearly luster; -- so called from Fiora, in Ischia.","pos":""}],"FIORITURE":[{"def":"Little flowers of ornament introduced into a melody by a singer or player.","pos":""}]}